Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reset_timing_derate(25.10)                          reset_timing_derate(25.10)

Name
       reset_timing_derate  - Resets derate factors specified on a design or a
       list of instances (cells, net, or library cells)

Syntax
       reset_timing_derate

       [-delay_corner <delayCornerName>]

       [-increment]

       [<object_list>]

       Resets derate factors specified on a design  or  a  list  of  instances
       (cells,  net,  or library cells). All the derating factors that are set
       globally or on specific instances are reset to a default value of 1.0.

       The derating factors for early or late paths in the design are set  us-
       ing the set_timing_derate command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -delay_corner <delayCornerName>
              Specifies  the  delay corner or a list of delay corners on which
              reset derating is to be applied.

       -increment
              Resets the incremental derate values  that  are  set  using  the
              set_timing_derate command.

              The  set_timing_derate  command saves two different values - the
              "base" derate and the "incremental" derate. When the  -incremen-
              tal  parameter  is  used, the software populates the incremental
              derates.  The reset_timing_derate command will reset the  incre-
              mental derate values only.

       <object_list>
              Specifies the list of cells, nets, or library cells to reset.

              If  the <object_list> contains hierarchical cells then all cells
              within the hierarchical cells and across lower hierarchies  have
              reset derate factors.

Examples
              * The  following  example  resets  all  the  object-specific and
                global derating factors:

                reset_timing_derate *

              * The following example resets only global derating factors:

                reset_timing_derate [current_design]

              * The following example resets derating factor  values  for  the
                specified delay corner:

                reset_timing_derate -delay_corner<delayCornerName>

              * The  following  example  resets the global derating values for
                the specified delay corner:

                reset_timing_derate    -delay_corner<delayCornerName>    [cur-
                rent_design]

              * The following example resets timing derate on instance u1:

                reset_timing_derate [get_cells u1]

Related Information
